WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.560
You've known it when before everything was knocked down, Loudon Square and all of that,

00:00:06.560 --> 00:00:10.840
and now what did it feel like? They knocked it down?

00:00:10.840 --> 00:00:16.040
Oh, well, you know what? Did you know the... Oh, what was he?

00:00:16.040 --> 00:00:20.640
Dunleavy his name was. I think he was a councillor or something.

00:00:20.640 --> 00:00:27.040
You know, if he was down in his poppins for my mother's and they'd say they were sorry after.

00:00:27.080 --> 00:00:31.320
You know, they pulled them all down. They were sorry.

00:00:31.320 --> 00:00:34.920
There were some wonderful houses. Loudon Square was glorious.

00:00:34.920 --> 00:00:41.560
Oh, yeah. Well, I mean, my father used to say all the captains and when he came here,

00:00:41.560 --> 00:00:47.760
there was all captains in that living in Loudon Square, you know, from the seaman.

00:00:47.760 --> 00:00:50.640
The key people, the captains of Seaman.

00:00:50.640 --> 00:00:57.880
And he said he held his steps going up to the houses before they pulled them all down.

00:00:57.880 --> 00:01:02.560
With your extended family, all of the sports stars.

00:01:02.560 --> 00:01:07.400
I mean, you know, it seems like every single one of them was a sports star.

00:01:07.400 --> 00:01:12.720
That's it. That's it. But of course, I mean, we're the pride of this.

00:01:12.720 --> 00:01:15.480
They couldn't play for Wales.

00:01:15.480 --> 00:01:17.000
No.

00:01:17.040 --> 00:01:21.080
None of them. I bet they were sorry after.

00:01:21.080 --> 00:01:25.920
Well, yeah, you had talent like Johnny, who went north.

00:01:25.920 --> 00:01:28.280
You know.

00:01:28.280 --> 00:01:31.680
Yeah, you often look up my brother. He was good.

00:01:31.680 --> 00:01:34.320
Yeah. He was good.

00:01:34.320 --> 00:01:41.920
They said, because when he passed, a lot of them come down from Yorkshire.

00:01:41.920 --> 00:01:47.640
I mean, none of them was given a eulogy, you know, in the church.

00:01:47.640 --> 00:01:52.640
And he said, no one has passed him yet, the gold.

00:01:52.640 --> 00:01:54.160
Johnny.

00:01:54.160 --> 00:01:55.600
Yeah.

00:01:55.600 --> 00:01:59.840
And they loved Billy Boston and Barry Wiggins.

00:01:59.840 --> 00:02:02.840
Yeah. I mean, it's crazy.

00:02:02.840 --> 00:02:09.200
They adore him up north and Cardiff don't even honour him.

00:02:09.200 --> 00:02:10.880
No.

00:02:10.920 --> 00:02:14.000
And there can only be a couple of reasons for that.

00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:15.800
Of course.

00:02:15.800 --> 00:02:16.720
Of course.

00:02:16.720 --> 00:02:18.880
Yeah.

00:02:18.880 --> 00:02:24.600
So what about you and family? You said you had your boy Craig.

00:02:24.600 --> 00:02:25.680
Yes.

00:02:25.680 --> 00:02:30.400
So what about your family?

00:02:30.400 --> 00:02:31.680
Craig passed away.

00:02:31.680 --> 00:02:33.520
Right.

00:02:33.520 --> 00:02:36.240
He was only 40.

00:02:36.240 --> 00:02:38.400
I'm sorry to hear that, love. I didn't know.

00:02:38.400 --> 00:02:39.400
Yeah.

00:02:39.400 --> 00:02:41.120
Oh, everybody loved Craig.

00:02:41.120 --> 00:02:41.920
Yeah.

00:02:41.920 --> 00:02:52.800
He, you know, he had a good education, but he wanted to be in the airline.

00:02:52.800 --> 00:02:54.240
You know.

00:02:54.240 --> 00:02:56.520
He wanted to be in the airline.

00:02:56.520 --> 00:03:02.480
And then he went in the airline after.

00:03:02.480 --> 00:03:03.920
Yeah, and he liked it.

00:03:03.920 --> 00:03:05.600
Right.

00:03:05.640 --> 00:03:07.880
And everybody loved Craig.

00:03:07.880 --> 00:03:11.240
Yeah.

00:03:11.240 --> 00:03:12.920
Oh dear.

00:03:12.920 --> 00:03:13.800
Yeah.

00:03:13.800 --> 00:03:14.240
Yeah.

00:03:14.240 --> 00:03:16.640
He's a.

00:03:16.640 --> 00:03:21.040
There are sad times and there are good times.

00:03:21.040 --> 00:03:22.080
Oh, yes.

00:03:22.080 --> 00:03:24.640
Yes.

