What about the way, one of the things a lot of people

00:10:04.920 --> 00:10:09.960
have talked about is manners and the way people have always

00:10:09.960 --> 00:10:13.120
respected older people, auntie and uncle.

00:10:13.120 --> 00:10:13.960
Oh, yeah.

00:10:13.960 --> 00:10:15.680
Oh, yeah.

00:10:15.720 --> 00:10:19.840
Because a girl says we run, in my convenience again,

00:10:19.840 --> 00:10:21.640
I wanted a job there.

00:10:21.640 --> 00:10:26.360
She says, we call you, you got some auntie, haven't you?

00:10:26.360 --> 00:10:27.720
I said, no.

00:10:27.720 --> 00:10:30.200
I said, we knew her good.

00:10:30.200 --> 00:10:33.400
And we didn't need to call her by her name.

00:10:33.400 --> 00:10:35.320
And so we used to call her auntie.

00:10:35.320 --> 00:10:35.840
Yeah.

00:10:35.840 --> 00:10:38.280
So I said, oh, and she next to myself, gosh,

00:10:38.280 --> 00:10:41.040
you got some auntie.

00:10:41.040 --> 00:10:42.960
But I did that so we was, you know.

00:10:42.960 --> 00:10:45.400
Yeah, it's respect, you know.

00:10:46.080 --> 00:10:49.840
As a child, you couldn't call them by their first name.

00:10:49.840 --> 00:10:52.240
No, no, no, no.

00:10:52.240 --> 00:10:54.600
No.

00:10:54.600 --> 00:11:02.240
Yeah, but as I said, nobody had loads of money or nothing

00:11:02.240 --> 00:11:03.480
like that.

00:11:03.480 --> 00:11:04.360
You know what I mean?

00:11:04.360 --> 00:11:06.680
But you still have the good life.

00:11:06.680 --> 00:11:07.200
Yeah.

00:11:07.200 --> 00:11:11.160
When we were kids, yeah, my father went to sea.

00:11:11.200 --> 00:11:16.720
And I always remember, Bill and Keith,

00:11:16.720 --> 00:11:20.360
a fellow that was in charge, one of them, with the ships

00:11:20.360 --> 00:11:22.000
and all, because he used to come up,

00:11:22.000 --> 00:11:24.880
and he'd say, oh, John, this fellow can't go.

00:11:24.880 --> 00:11:29.480
He said, would you take his place?

00:11:29.480 --> 00:11:32.320
So dad said, well, I'm going to love it time.

00:11:32.320 --> 00:11:34.040
And he said, we'll catch the train and so on.

00:11:34.040 --> 00:11:37.600
So anyway, dad, I missed the train.

00:11:37.600 --> 00:11:39.920
And he came back, and he got in touch with Bill.

00:11:39.960 --> 00:11:42.040
And he said, I missed the train.

00:11:42.040 --> 00:11:43.760
He said, I won't make it.

00:11:43.760 --> 00:11:45.160
So it's a good job.

00:11:45.160 --> 00:11:50.360
He never think of throwing that ship he would have been on.

00:11:50.360 --> 00:11:52.320
Yeah.

00:11:52.320 --> 00:11:57.280
That's just the way your luck runs sometimes, isn't it?

00:11:57.280 --> 00:11:59.640
Yeah, he missed the train.

00:11:59.640 --> 00:12:02.880
And then I said, oh, I'm telling him,

00:12:02.880 --> 00:12:06.040
my I'm not catching the next one.

00:12:06.040 --> 00:12:07.360
He couldn't have done it anyway.

00:12:07.360 --> 00:12:08.600
He couldn't have gone.

00:12:08.640 --> 00:12:12.320
He missed the boat.

