Because my my granddad, he was from Barbados and he went.

00:12:48.280 --> 00:12:51.400
He was on the ships all the way through the First World War.

00:12:51.400 --> 00:12:54.320
He then he then became a miner

00:12:54.320 --> 00:12:57.520
at just the beginning of the Second World War,

00:12:57.520 --> 00:13:01.240
because my nan said, you are not going again.

00:13:01.240 --> 00:13:04.360
Because you went, you live through one.

00:13:04.360 --> 00:13:06.200
You'll never live through another.

00:13:06.200 --> 00:13:08.000
She wouldn't let him go.

00:13:08.000 --> 00:13:11.080
And it's typical, it's typical luck.

00:13:11.080 --> 00:13:14.960
You know, you can't be a merchant seamen, which is hard enough life.

00:13:14.960 --> 00:13:18.480
So what do you do? You become a miner.

00:13:18.480 --> 00:13:24.080
Yeah, it gets you good enough, because in the world we.

